   "metadata": {
    "id": "-vsMzt_np1ck"
   },
   "source": [
    "Ranking and bar-charting the top-N months by volatility is a focused way to highlight the specific extreme events buried inside the full time series line chart."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "8zGJKyg5p1ck"
   },
   "source": [
    "##### 2. What is/are the insight(s) found from the chart?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "ZYdMsrqVp1ck"
   },
   "source": [
    "8 of the 10 most volatile months fall within or right around the 2018-2020 crisis window (the remainder being 2008 financial-crisis months) — concretely proving the crisis, not normal market activity, produced the stock's most extreme price swings."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "PVzmfK_Ep1ck"
   },
   "source": [
    "##### 3. Will the gained insights help creating a positive business impact?\n",
    "Are there any insights that lead to negative growth? Justify with specific reason."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "druuKYZpp1ck"
   },
   "source": [
    "Yes — this is strong quantitative evidence (not just a visual impression) that governance risk, not general market risk, was the dominant driver of extreme volatility for this stock — an important distinction for risk attribution."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "n3dbpmDWp1ck"
   },
   "source": [
    "#### Chart - 12"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "bwevp1tKp1ck"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Chart - 12 visualization code\n",
    "comparison = df.groupby('Crisis_Period')[['Close','HL_diff','pct_change']].mean()\n",
    "comparison.index = ['Non-Crisis Period','Crisis Period']\n",
    "comparison['Close'].plot(kind='bar', color=['steelblue','red'], figsize=(7,5))\n",
    "plt.title('Average Closing Price: Crisis vs Non-Crisis Period')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Average Close (INR)')\n",
    "plt.xticks(rotation=0)\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "comparison"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "ylSl6qgtp1ck"
   },
   "source": [
    "##### 1. Why did you pick the specific chart?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "m2xqNkiQp1ck"
   },
   "source": [
    "A grouped bar chart comparing a numeric variable's mean across a binary categorical flag (`Crisis_Period`) is a direct way to quantify the difference the earlier charts suggested visually — and it feeds straight into the formal hypothesis test performed later."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "ZWILFDl5p1ck"
   },
   "source": [
    "##### 2. What is/are the insight(s) found from the chart?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "x-lUsV2mp1ck"
   },
   "source": [
    "Average closing price during the crisis period is dramatically lower than during the non-crisis period, and average volatility (`HL_diff`) is meaningfully higher — confirming both a level shift and a volatility shift caused by the crisis."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "M7G43BXep1ck"
   },
   "source": [
    "##### 3. Will the gained insights help creating a positive business impact?\n",
    "Are there any insights that lead to negative growth? Justify with specific reason."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "5wwDJXsLp1cl"
   },
   "source": [
    "Yes — this table is the direct evidence base for Hypothesis Statements 1 and 3 tested later in the notebook, and for any client-facing summary needing a single, defensible number for 'how much did the crisis cost investors'."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "Ag9LCva-p1cl"
   },
   "source": [
    "#### Chart - 13"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "EUfxeq9-p1cl"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Chart - 13 visualization code\n",
    "zoom = df[(df['Date'] >= '2017-01-01') & (df['Date'] <= '2020-11-01')]\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(14,6))\n",
    "plt.plot(zoom['Date'], zoom['Close'], marker='o', color='darkred')\n",
    "plt.axvline(pd.Timestamp('2018-09-01'), color='black', linestyle='--', label='Crisis Onset (Sep 2018)')\n",
    "plt.title('Zoomed View: Closing Price 2017 - 2020 (Crisis Detail)')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Date'); plt.ylabel('Closing Price (INR)')\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "E6MkPsBcp1cl"
   },
   "source": [
    "##### 1. Why did you pick the specific chart?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "V22bRsFWp1cl"
   },
   "source": [
    "Zooming the time-series line chart into just the 2017-2020 window (multivariate view of time + price + a marked event date) gives the fine-grained detail that the full 15-year chart compresses too much to see clearly."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "2cELzS2fp1cl"
   },
   "source": [
    "##### 2. What is/are the insight(s) found from the chart?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "ozQPc2_Ip1cl"
   },
   "source": [
    "The decline is not a single crash but happens in **distinct steps**: a sharp fall in Sep 2018, a partial recovery into early 2019, a second collapse through mid-2019, and a final drop to single digits around the March 2020 RBI moratorium."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "3MPXvC8up1cl"
   },
   "source": [
    "##### 3. Will the gained insights help creating a positive business impact?\n",
    "Are there any insights that lead to negative growth? Justify with specific reason."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "GL8l1tdLp1cl"
   },
   "source": [
    "Yes — recognizing that the crash happened in stages (not one event) is important for anyone building a monitoring system: multiple independent 'trigger points' existed where risk indicators could have flagged trouble, not just one moment."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "NC_X3p0fY2L0"
   },
   "source": [
    "#### Chart - 14 - Correlation Heatmap"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "xyC9zolEZNRQ"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Correlation Heatmap visualization code\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10,8))\n",
    "numeric_cols = ['Open','High','Low','Close','HL_diff','OC_diff','pct_change','Close_lag1','Close_lag2','MA_3','MA_6']\n",
    "sns.heatmap(df[numeric_cols].corr(), annot=True, fmt='.2f', cmap='coolwarm', square=True)\n",
    "plt.title('Correlation Heatmap - All Numeric Features')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "UV0SzAkaZNRQ"
   },
   "source": [
    "##### 1. Why did you pick the specific chart?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "DVPuT8LYZNRQ"
   },
   "source": [
    "A correlation heatmap is the standard multivariate chart for quickly spotting linear relationships and redundancy (multicollinearity) across every pair of numeric features at once."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "YPEH6qLeZNRQ"
   },
   "source": [
    "##### 2. What is/are the insight(s) found from the chart?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "bfSqtnDqZNRR"
   },
   "source": [
    "`Open`, `High`, `Low`, `Close`, `Close_lag1`, `Close_lag2`, `MA_3` and `MA_6` are all very strongly correlated with each other (>0.95) as expected, while `HL_diff`, `OC_diff` and `pct_change` are comparatively weakly correlated with `Close` — meaning they add genuinely new information rather than duplicating the price-level features."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "q29F0dvdveiT"
   },
   "source": [
    "#### Chart - 15 - Pair Plot"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "o58-TEIhveiU"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Pair Plot visualization code\n",
    "sns.pairplot(df[['Open','High','Low','Close','HL_diff','pct_change']], diag_kind='kde', corner=True)\n",
    "plt.suptitle('Pair Plot of Key Numeric Features', y=1.02)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "EXh0U9oCveiU"
   },
   "source": [
    "##### 1. Why did you pick the specific chart?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "eMmPjTByveiU"
   },
   "source": [
    "A pair plot extends the correlation heatmap by showing the *actual shape* of every pairwise relationship (not just a single correlation number) plus each variable's own distribution on the diagonal — useful multivariate confirmation before modeling."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "22aHeOlLveiV"
   },
   "source": [
    "##### 2. What is/are the insight(s) found from the chart?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "uPQ8RGwHveiV"
   },
   "source": [
    "The Open/High/Low/Close scatter panels all show tight, near-linear diagonal bands (confirming the heatmap's high correlations), while `HL_diff` and `pct_change` scatter far more loosely against price — visually confirming they capture a different kind of signal (volatility/momentum) rather than just price level."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "JcMwzZxoAimU"
   },
   "source": [
    "## **5. Solution to Business Objective**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "8G2x9gOozGDZ"
   },
   "source": [
    "#### What do you suggest the client to achieve Business Objective ?\n",
    "Explain Briefly."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "pASKb0qOza21"
   },
   "source": [
    "To achieve the business objective, the recommended approach is to feed the engineered momentum\n",
    "and volatility features (previous month's close, 3/6-month moving averages, high-low spread,\n",
    "percentage return) into a regression model — a follow-on Machine Learning notebook in this\n",
    "submission set builds and compares exactly such models (Linear Regression, Random Forest and\n",
    "XGBoost) and selects the best one via cross-validated hyperparameter tuning. For monitoring\n",
    "purposes, the client should track `HL_diff` (volatility) as an early-warning indicator, since this\n",
    "project's analysis shows it spiked sharply and consistently ahead of/during the worst points of the\n",
    "2018-2020 crisis — a rising `HL_diff` alongside a downward `MA_3`/`MA_6` crossover is a concrete,\n",
    "data-driven signal worth monitoring in near-real-time for early risk detection.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "gCX9965dhzqZ"
   },
   "source": [
    "# **Conclusion**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "Fjb1IsQkh3yE"
   },
   "source": [
    "This EDA of Yes Bank's monthly stock prices (2005-2020) shows a clean, complete dataset whose\n",
    "five raw columns hide a rich underlying story once engineered features are added. The stock enjoyed\n",
    "over a decade of strong, fairly steady growth, peaking above ₹390 in mid-2018, before collapsing by\n",
    "over 95% within about 18 months following the co-founder fraud allegations and the eventual RBI\n",
    "moratorium. Correlation analysis confirmed the four OHLC columns are highly collinear, motivating the\n",
    "creation of volatility (`HL_diff`), momentum (`Close_lag1/2`) and trend (`MA_3`, `MA_6`) features that\n",
    "carry genuinely new information. The 15 charts above — spanning univariate, bivariate and\n",
    "multivariate views — consistently point to the same conclusion: the 2018-2020 period was\n",
    "**qualitatively different**, not just quantitatively lower, from the rest of the stock's history,\n",
    "with both price level and volatility shifting sharply. These findings set up the follow-on Machine\n",
    "Learning notebook, where a regression model is built and tuned to predict the closing price using\n",
    "exactly the features whose importance was uncovered here.\n"
   ]
  },
